            </persName>
            <birth when="1752"/>
            <death when="1825"/>
            <note>Genevan natural philosopher and journal editor. Corresponded with Davy. ForMemRSL.</note>
         </person>
         <person xml:id="person_864">
            <persName xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0">
               <forename type="first">Pierre</forename>
               <surname>Prevost</surname>
            </persName>
            <birth when="1751"/>
            <death when="1839"/>
            <note>A Genevan philosopher and physicist. In 1791 he explained Pictet's experiment by arguing that all bodies radiate heat, no matter how hot or cold they are.</note>
         </person>
         <person xml:id="person_581">
            <persName xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0">
